Problem 3. (6 pt) Describe the problem of overlapping and the way of solving it using this dataset. Show it using appropriate tools via R. 

ggplot(Data,aes(mppwt,bweight,colour=smoker)) + geom_point(size=8)+
  labs(title = "Weight of baby (lbs) vs Mothers pre-pregnancy weight (lbs)",y="Weight of baby",x="Mothers pre-pregnancy weight")

## one of the ways to handle overlapping is making size smaller
ggplot(Data,aes(mppwt,bweight,colour=smoker)) + geom_point(size=8)+
  labs(title = "Weight of baby (lbs) vs Mothers pre-pregnancy weight (lbs)",y="Weight of baby",x="Mothers pre-pregnancy weight")

ggplot(Data, aes(x=smoker, y=bweight,group=smoker)) +
  geom_boxplot(color="black",outlier.colour = "red")+
  geom_jitter(position=position_jitter(0.2))# as we see smoking really effects on baby's weight negatively,there is no outliers

# For boxplot when we use geom_jitter we can see correct distribution.
Problem 4. (9 pt) Use at least 3 variables for this task.

  1. Find the meaningful pattern between the weight of baby and the other variables, add an element of descriptive statistics on graphics. 

#1
ggplot(Data,aes(mnocig,bweight,colour=smoker))+geom_point(size=3)+
  geom_smooth(method="lm",se=FALSE,size=1.5,col='red')+
  ggtitle("Scatterplot of babies weight and number of cigarretes per day") + 
  xlab("Cigarretes per day ") +
  ylab("Baby's weight")

#number of cigarretes influence on baby's weight negatively 


#2
ggplot(Data,aes(gestation,bweight,colour=smoker))+geom_point(size=3)+
  geom_smooth(method="lm",se=FALSE,size=1.5,col='red')+
  ggtitle("Scatterplot of babies weight and gestation relationship") + 
  xlab("Gestation ") +
  ylab("Baby's weight")

#number of weeks influence on baby's weight positively

#3
ggplot(Data,aes(mppwt,bweight,colour=mage35)) + geom_point(size=3)+
  geom_smooth(method="lm",se=FALSE,size=1.5,col='red')+
  ggtitle("Scatterplot of babies weight and mother's pre-pregnancy weight  by age factor") + 
  xlab("Mother's pre-pregnancy weight ") +
  ylab("Baby's weight")

#mother's pre-pregnancy weight influence on baby's weight positively
